cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.HC. 

The paper focuses on evaluating the performance of GANs in generating images that are more consistent with human perception of image quality. This involves the use of brain signals to develop an evaluation metric called Neuroscore. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper proposes a convolutional neural network (CNN) based neuro-AI interface, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the comparison of Neuroscore with existing evaluation metrics, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the use of brain signals to develop an evaluation metric reflects the sub-category of cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
